);

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;


##########################
#  Setup

$a=random(-6,-2,1);
$b=random(.15,.75,.1);

$gr = init_graph(-10,-10,10,10,
axes=>[0,0],
grid=>[10,10],
size=>[600,600]
);

$gr1 = init_graph(-10,-10,10,10,
axes=>[0,0],
grid=>[10,10],
size=>[600,600]
);


$gr2 = init_graph(-10,-10,10,10,
axes=>[0,0],
grid=>[10,10],
size=>[600,600]
);

$gr3 = init_graph(-10,-10,10,10,
axes=>[0,0],
grid=>[10,10],
size=>[600,600]
);

$gr4 = init_graph(-10,-10,10,10,
axes=>[0,0],
grid=>[10,10],
size=>[600,600]
);

add_functions($gr, "$a($b)^x for x in <-6,10>" . 
  " using color:blue and weight:2");

add_functions($gr1, "$a($b)^-x for x in <-10,6>" . 
  " using color:blue and weight:2");

add_functions($gr2, "-$a($b)^(x) for x in <-6,10>" . 
  " using color:blue and weight:2");

add_functions($gr3, "-$a($b)^(-x) for x in <-10,8>" . 
  " using color:blue and weight:2");

add_functions($gr4, "-$a(3*$b)^(x) for x in <-10,10>" . 
  " using color:blue and weight:2");

Context("Numeric");

Context("Numeric");
$popup1 = PopUp(
  ["?","A","B", "C", "D"], "B",
);

$fun=("$a($b)^x");

$ans1=("-$fun");


Context("LimitedPoint");
$ans2 = List( Point("(0,-$a)"));


#################################
#  Main text

BEGIN_PGML


The graph of [`f(x)=[$fun]`] is given below (click on graph to enlarge):


>>[@ image(insertGraph($gr), width=>300, height=>300), @]*<<



Let [`g(x)`] be the reflection of [`f(x)`] across the [`x`]-axis.  Which of the following graphs represents the graph of [`g(x)`]? [_________________]{$popup1} 


>>A. [@ image(insertGraph($gr1), width=>200, height=>200), @]*   B. [@ image(insertGraph($gr2), width=>200, height=>200), @]* <<  

>>C. [@ image(insertGraph($gr3), width=>200, height=>200), @]*  D. [@ image(insertGraph($gr4), width=>200, height=>200), @]*   <<

What is the equation for [`g(x)`]?  [`g(x)`]= [_________________]{$ans1} [@ AnswerFormatHelp("formulas") @]*

What is the [`y`]-intercept of [`g(x)`]?  Enter an ordered pair for the intercept. [_________________]{$ans2} [@ AnswerFormatHelp("points") @]*


END_PGML

